task:
Unauthenticated read access on policy endpoints

handleListPolicies, handlePolicyDetail (line 159), and handleGetVersionHistory (line 404) perform no authentication or authorization check before returning policy data. Any HTTP client — authenticated or not — can enumerate all policies in any workspace they know the ID of.

The PR describes authorization guards restricting mutations to human identities, but read endpoints should still require a valid session. Even if read access is intentionally permitted to agents, it should at minimum be restricted to authenticated identities that are members of the workspace.

Compare with the mutation guard pattern already used:

// Current (no auth at all):
async function handleListPolicies(deps, workspaceId, request) {
  const workspaceOrError = await resolveWorkspace(...);
  // immediately lists policies — no session check
  ...
}

// Suggested (require authenticated session):
async function handleListPolicies(deps, workspaceId, request) {
  const identityOrError = await resolveIdentityFromSession(deps, request);
  if (isResponse(identityOrError)) return identityOrError;
  // now resolve workspace and list
  ...
}
The same fix applies to handlePolicyDetail (line 159) and handleGetVersionHistory (line 404).

